PR12 view influence attribution patch
=====================================

This patch is applied after PR7 and PR8:

  python scripts/third_party/apply_gaussian_splatting_observation_patch.py \
    --third-party-root ./third_party \
    --patch pr12_view_influence_attribution

The generated patch adds marker-delimited, observation-only hooks to the local
official Gaussian Splatting `train.py` clone.

Markers:

  # VIEWTRUST PR12 VIEW INFLUENCE START
  # VIEWTRUST PR12 VIEW INFLUENCE END

Safety policy:

  - no loss changes
  - no optimizer changes
  - no camera sampling changes
  - no rendering changes
  - no densification threshold or decision changes
  - no pruning or opacity reset decision changes
  - no third_party source is committed to ViewTrust-GS

PR12 behavior:

  - sampled view identity is added to PR7 iteration_metrics rows
  - fields include view_name, camera_uid, and view_split
  - PR8 lifecycle birth/prune events receive the active sampled-view context
  - context is cleared after the densification/pruning block

This is temporal/source-view attribution, not exact per-pixel contribution
attribution and not a trust score.
